I"}<p>The job of a PM is to be a truth seeker.</p>
<ul>
  <li>It means digging deep and understanding your customers. I mean really talking to your customers, understanding their JTBDs, and not just relying on the surveys that your Research team sends.</li>
  <li>It means not taking data and face value and understanding biases that might cloud the output.</li>
  <li>It means ask WHY again and again.</li>
  <li>It means not talking timelines at face value.</li>
  <li>It means doing a RCA whenever there is a dip in conversion.</li>
  <li>It means doing pre-mortems and post-mortems.</li>
  <li>It means doing retrospectives.</li>
</ul>
